Oracle Autonomous Database offers a flexible pricing model based on ECPUs (Elastic CPUs), allowing organizations to pay for compute resources on an hourly basis. For instance, the cost for Oracle Autonomous Transaction Processing is $0.336 per ECPU per hour, with storage priced at $0.1156 per gigabyte per month. Additionally, Oracle provides a Bring Your Own License (BYOL) option, enabling customers to leverage existing licenses at a reduced rate of $0.0807 per ECPU per hour. Features like Elastic Pools allow consolidation of multiple databases, potentially reducing compute costs by up to 87%. These pricing structures, combined with automated management and scaling, contribute to significant cost efficiency for businesses. 
